	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: GameBoy(Color) Programming</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This probably should go <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewforum.php?f=20" class="postlink">here</a>.<br /><br />The GB/GBC uses a custom Z80 variant, so go get a Z80 assembler and look up the differences. Many assemblers have specific support for this variant (usually labeled as GBZ80), so that's something to take into account to save effort.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
