	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: GameBoy(Color) Programming</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The most popular assemblers are RGBDS (<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://otakunozoku.com/rednex-gameboy-development-system/">http://otakunozoku.com/rednex-gameboy-d ... nt-system/</a><!-- m -->) and WLA. You can find lots of information on <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gbdev.gg8.se/wiki/articles/Main_Page">http://gbdev.gg8.se/wiki/articles/Main_Page</a><!-- m --> and the Pan Doc (I'm not linking to it because I'm not sure it'll be the latest version). I think the official English Game Boy development manual was leaked. There are also some guides if you google.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

