		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You should probably use RGBDS, just because there's so much more GB code online written for it than WLA.<br /><br />Don't believe me? Look here. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://devrs.com/gb/asmcode.php#asmmath">http://devrs.com/gb/asmcode.php#asmmath</a><!-- m --> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gameboy.mongenel.com/asmschool.html">http://gameboy.mongenel.com/asmschool.html</a><!-- m --> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://cratel.wichita.edu/cratel/ECE238Spr08">http://cratel.wichita.edu/cratel/ECE238Spr08</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Although if it were my choice, WLA would certainly be the assembler of choice, unless you take its bugs into accommodation.

		

